"688","<FILENAME>auditletter.txt"
"689","<DESCRIPTION>AUDIT LETTER"
"690","<TEXT>"
"691","Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting"
"692","Firm"
"693","To the Shareholders and"
"694","The Board of Trustees of"
"695","Federated Income Securities Trust:"
"696","In planning and performing our audits of the financial"
"697","statements of Federated Prudent DollarBear Fund, a"
"698","portfolio of Federated Income Securities Trust (the"
"699","Fund) as of and for the year ended September 30, 2011,"
"700","in accordance with the standards of the Public Company"
"701","Accounting Oversight Board (United States), we"
"702","considered the Fund?s internal control over financial"
"703","reporting, including controls over safeguarding"
"704","securities, as a basis for designing our auditing"
"705","procedures for the purpose of expressing our opinion on"
"706","the financial statements and to comply with the"
"707","requirements of Form N-SAR, but not for the purpose of"
"708","expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of the Fund?s"
"709","internal control over financial reporting. Accordingly,"
"710","we express no such opinion."
"711","Management of the Fund is responsible for establishing"
"712","and maintaining effective internal control over financial"
"713","reporting. In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates and"
"714","judgments by management are required to assess the"
"715","expected benefits and related costs of controls. A"
"716","company?s internal control over financial reporting is a"
"717","process designed to provide reasonable assurance"
"718","regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the"
"719","preparation of financial statements for external purposes"
"720","in accordance with generally accepted accounting"
"721","principles. A company?s internal control over financial"
"722","reporting includes those policies and procedures that (1)"
"723","pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable"
"724","detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and"
"725","dispositions of the assets of the company; (2) provide"
"726","reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as"
"727","necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in"
"728","accordance with generally accepted accounting"
"729","principles, and that receipts and expenditures of the"
"730","company are being made in accordance with"
"731","authorizations of management and Trustees of the"
"732","company; and (3) provide reasonable assurance"
"733","regarding prevention or timely detection of the"
"734","unauthorized acquisition, use, or disposition of the"
"735","company?s assets that could have a material effect on the"
"736","financial statements."
"737","Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over"
"738","financial reporting may not prevent or detect"
"739","misstatements. Also, projections of any evaluation of"
"740","effectiveness to future periods are subject to the risk that"
"741","controls may become inadequate because of changes in"
"742","conditions, or that the degree of compliance with the"
"743","policies or procedures may deteriorate."
"744","A deficiency in internal control over financial reporting"
"745","exists when the design or operation of a control does not"
"746","allow management or employees, in the normal course"
"747","of performing their assigned functions, to prevent or"
"748","detect misstatements on a timely basis. A material"
"749","weakness is a deficiency, or a combination of"
"750","deficiencies, in internal control over financial reporting,"
"751","such that there is a reasonable possibility that a material"
"752","misstatement of the Fund?s annual or interim financial"
"753","statements will not be prevented or detected on a timely"
"754","basis."
"755","Our consideration of the Fund?s internal control over"
"756","financial reporting was for the limited purpose described"
"757","in the first paragraph and would not necessarily disclose"
"758","all deficiencies in internal control that might be material"
"759","weaknesses under standards established by the Public"
"760","Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States)."
"761","However, we noted no deficiencies in the Fund?s"
"762","internal control over financial reporting and its"
"763","operation, including controls over safeguarding"
"764","securities that we consider to be a material weakness as"
"765","defined above as of September 30, 2011."
"766","This report is intended solely for the information and use"
"767","of management and the Board of Trustees of Federated"
"768","Income Securities Trust and the Securities and Exchange"
"769","Commission and is not intended to be and should not be"
"770","used by anyone other than those specified parties."
"771","Boston, Massachusetts"
"772","November 22, 2011"
